Package: pleior
Type: Package
Title: Pleiotropy Analysis for GWAS Data
Version: 0.99.0
Date: 2025-01-14
Authors@R:
    person("Dany", "Mukesha", , "danymukesha@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Tools for identifying and analyzing pleiotropic genetic variants
    in genome-wide association studies (GWAS). Pleiotropy occurs when
    a single genetic variant influences multiple traits, offering insights
    into shared biological pathways and disease relationships.
    Includes functions for data loading, preprocessing, pleiotropy detection,
    and comprehensive visualization including Manhattan plots, heatmaps, network graphs,
    and publication-ready figures. The package includes a curated subset of real GWAS
    catalog data (~2,500 associations across 15 traits) demonstrating multi-trait
    genetic variants.
